Description. Apterous male ( holotype ) (
Figs. 1 A, B, D
) Body length 5.82 , width (across mesoacetabula) 1.93 . Body narrower than female.

Head. Length: Head 0.94 , antennal segments one to four 1.78 , 1.55 , 2.01 , 3.01 ; rostral segments one to four 0.31 , 0.16 , 1.64 , 0.34 . Width: Head 1.29 ; head width between eyes 0.69 . Head with pair of lateral shorter stripes and central longer V-shaped stripe, no stripes uniting anteriorly (
Fig. 1 A
). Subapex medially with pair of piceous spots covered by brown hue. Antennae much longer than body. Rostrum reaching to middle of mesosternum (
Fig. 1 B
); apical flap of third rostral segment and fourth rostral segment fully black and shiny.

Thorax. Length: Anterior pronotal lobe 0.61 ; pronotal lobe 2.52 ; prosternum 0.58 ; mesosternum 2.41 , metasternum 0.45 ; fore femora 2.39 ; fore tibia 2.14 ; fore tarsus I 0.19 ; fore tarsus II 0.26 ; mid femora 6.18 ; mid tibia 4.33 ; mid tarsus I 1.98 ; mid tarsus II 0.43 ; hind femora 6.08 ; hind tibia 2.74 ; hind tarsus I 0.51 ; hind tarsus II 0.35 . Width: Pronotal lobe 0.96 ; fore femora 0.24 , mid femora 0.17 , hind femora 0.13 . Pronotum and mesonotum with median and marginal stripes; mesopleuron with distinct stripe very close to pronotal lobe and obscure stripe on middle of mesopleuron; black stripe on sublateral region of mesosternum originating near base of fore trochanter and reaching near anterior region of mesoacetabular groove and not interrupted medially (
Fig. 1 D
); piceous spot on mesoacetabula open anteriorly; indistinct stripe on sublateral region of mesonotum brown; metacetabulum near to connexivum with curved piceous stripe; posterior margin of metasternum slightly sinuated laterally and convexed at middle; omphalium protruding just above posterior margin of metasternum, surrounded with pale reddish hue; stripe on metanotum not reaching posterior margin; W-shaped marking between metanotum and first abdominal tergite black. Legs. Fore femora and fore tibiae slightly curved; apex of each middle femur with small spine; apices of hind coxae near fifth abdominal sternum.

Apterous female ( Paratypes ) (
Figs. 1 C, F
). Mean body length 6.52 , range 5.88–7.25 (n= 5 ), width (across mesoacetabula) 2.41 , range 2.13–2.76 (n= 5 ).

Macropterous female (
Fig. 1 E
). Mean body length 6.71 ( 6.42–6.93 ) (n= 3 ), width (across mesoacetabula) 2.27 ( 2.16–2.33 ) (n= 3 ).
